# Parallel Thesis Work

When the user requests work spanning **2+ independent thesis domains**, use `mcp_task` to dispatch subagents in parallel.

## Domain Pairs (Dispatch in Parallel)

| Domain A | Domain B | Example |
|----------|----------|---------|
| Citations | Writing | Resolve TODO-CITE + draft section |
| Simulation | Methodology | Run DTSE + update personC_methodology.tex |
| Review | Citations | Hostile review + reference resolution |
| Empirical | Results | empirical_analysis.tex + personC_results.tex |

## Subagent Types

- **explore** — Codebase search, file discovery
- **code-reviewer** — Hostile review, consistency, preflight
- **generalPurpose** — Citations, REFERENCE_MAPPING, drafting

## Do Not Parallelise When

- Tasks edit the same file
- One task depends on the output of another
- User explicitly asks for sequential work
